iquaire & the Connoisseur |accessdate= 2009-08-14 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20110203052336/http://www.lantiquaire.us/origins-of-mirrors.html |archive-date= 2011-02-03 |url-status= dead }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=fried2001>pp. 162\u2013164, ''Apollonius of Perga's Conica: text, context, subtext'', Michael N. Fried and [[Sabetai Unguru]], Brill, 2001, {{ISBN|90-04-11977-9}}.</ref>\n\n<ref name=greav1989>''Synchrotron Radiation Sources and Applications'' By G.N Greaves, I.H Munro -- Sussp Publishing 1989</ref>\n\n<ref name=hads1993>{{Cite journal |jstor = 1506387|title = The Tin-Mercury Mirror: Its Manufacturing Technique and Deterioration Processes|journal = Studies in Conservation|volume = 38|issue = 1|pages = 3\u201316|last1 = Hadsund|first1 = Per|year = 1993|doi=10.1179/sic.1993.38.1.3}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=holl2009>{{cite web |url= http://www.isnare.com/?aid=387476&ca=Advice |title= Mirrors |first= Patricia |last= Holland |publisher= Isnare Free Articles |accessdate= 2009-08-14}}</ref>\n\n<!--\n<ref name=hong2019>{{Cite web|url=https://hongjiaglass.com/product-item/silver-mirror/|title=Silver Mirror {{!}} Hongjia Architectural Glass Manufacturer|website=Hongjia Glass|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-19}}</ref>-->\n\n<ref name=hopk1910>{{cite book|author=Albert Allis Hopkins|title=The Scientific American cyclopedia of formulas: partly based upon the 28th ed. of Scientific American cyclopedia of receipts, notes and queries|url=https://archive.org/details/b31361523|year=1910|publisher=Munn & co., inc.|page=[https://archive.org/details/b31361523/page/89 89]}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=howm305>Episode 305 of [[How It's Made]], filmed at [http://www.laverreriewalker.com/ verrerie-walker.com] in [[Anjou, Quebec]], Canada</ref>\n\n<ref name=hurw2013>{{cite web|url=http://www.thisiscolossal.com/2013/01/the-skewed-anamorphic-sculptures-and-engineered-illusions-of-jonty-hurwitz/ |title=The skewed anamorphic sculptures and engineered illusions of Jonty Hurwitz |publisher